title: [Temple of Phoen, Courtyard]
description: Stretching from the flowerbeds along the esplanade to the walls of the temple, the courtyard wears a lush carpet of clover beneath the night sky.  The coiled domes of beehives stand near the temple's walls.

Stretching from the flowerbeds along the esplanade to the walls of the temple, the courtyard wears a lush carpet of clover.  Boasting more diminutive workers than the flowerbeds, the area is abuzz with life and purposeful activity to and from the coiled domes of the hives near the temple's walls.
